<item>
            <title>[SPR-7422] Document use of ApplicationEventPublisher</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-7422</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Section 3.13.2 (Standard and Custom Events) of the reference manual is out of date wrt best practices.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It does not talk about using ApplicationListener&amp;lt;T&amp;gt; with a type argument, thus removing instanceof checks in the event callback&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It does not espouse the use of ApplicationEventPublisher and ApplicationEventPublisherAware&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;In both cases, the javadoc for the corresponding bits is correct and up-to-date, it simply needs to be referenced in the manual.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
